{
    "xml": "<topic id=\"PHP3489\" outputclass=\"drug\" rev=\"1.12\" type=\"drug\" namespace=\"/drugs/neomycin-sulfate\" basename=\"neomycin-sulfate\" title=\"NEOMYCIN SULFATE\">\n<title>NEOMYCIN SULFATE</title>\n<body>\r\n<p outputclass=\"interactionsLinks\"> List of individual interactants: <xref format=\"dita\" href=\"#bnf_int_133\" namespace=\"/interactions/list-of-drug-interactions/antibacterials/aminoglycosides/neomycin\">Neomycin</xref>\n</p>\n<data name=\"vtmid\">73093001</data>\n<data name=\"primaryDomainOfEffect\">\n<data name=\"domainOfEffect\">  </data>\n</data>\n<data name=\"secondaryDomainsOfEffect\">\n<data name=\"domainOfEffect\">  </data>\r\n<data name=\"domainOfEffect\">  </data>\n</data>\r\n</body>\n<topic id=\"PHP52620\" outputclass=\"indicationsAndDose\" rev=\"1.31\" parent=\"/drugs/neomycin-sulfate\">\n<title>Indications and dose</title>\n<body>\n<section outputclass=\"indicationAndDoseGroup\">\n<sectiondiv outputclass=\"therapeuticIndications\">\n<p outputclass=\"therapeuticIndication\">Bacterial infection in otitis externa</p>\n</sectiondiv>\n<p outputclass=\"routesOfAdministration\">To the ear</p>\n<ul outputclass=\"patientGroups\">\n<li outputclass=\"patientGroup child\">\n<p>Child</p>\n<p>(consult product literature).</p>\n</li>\n<li outputclass=\"patientGroup adult\">\n<p>Adult</p>\n<p>(consult product literature).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section outputclass=\"indicationAndDoseGroup\">\n<sectiondiv outputclass=\"therapeuticIndications\">\n<p outputclass=\"therapeuticIndication\">Bacterial skin infections</p>\n</sectiondiv>\n<p outputclass=\"routesOfAdministration\">To the skin</p>\n<ul outputclass=\"patientGroups\">\n<li outputclass=\"patientGroup child\">\n<p>Child</p>\n<p>Apply up to 3 times a day, for short-term use only.</p>\n</li>\n<li outputclass=\"patientGroup adult\">\n<p>Adult</p>\n<p>Apply up to 3 times a day, for short-term use only.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section outputclass=\"indicationAndDoseGroup\">\n<sectiondiv outputclass=\"therapeuticIndications\">\n<p outputclass=\"therapeuticIndication\">Bowel sterilisation before surgery</p>\n</sectiondiv>\n<p outputclass=\"routesOfAdministration\">By mouth</p>\n<ul outputclass=\"patientGroups\">\n<li outputclass=\"patientGroup adult\">\n<p>Adult</p>\n<p>1&#8239;g every 1&#8239;hour for 4 hours, then 1&#8239;g every 4&#8239;hours for 2&#8211;3 days.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section outputclass=\"indicationAndDoseGroup\">\n<sectiondiv outputclass=\"therapeuticIndications\">\n<p outputclass=\"therapeuticIndication\">Hepatic coma</p>\n</sectiondiv>\n<p outputclass=\"routesOfAdministration\">By mouth</p>\n<ul outputclass=\"patientGroups\">\n<li outputclass=\"patientGroup adult\">\n<p>Adult</p>\n<p>Up to 4&#8239;g daily in divided doses usually for 5&#8211;7 days.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</body>\n</topic>\n<topic id=\"PHP52459\" outputclass=\"unlicensedUse\" rev=\"1.13\" parent=\"/drugs/neomycin-sulfate\">\n<title>Unlicensed use</title>\n<body>\n<section>\n<sectiondiv>\n<p outputclass=\"specificity\">With <ph outputclass=\"route\">topical</ph> use in children</p>\n<p>\n<i>Neomycin Cream BPC</i>&#8212;no information available.</p>\n</sectiondiv>\n</section>\n</body>\n</topic>\n<topic id=\"PHP52717\" outputclass=\"contraindications\" rev=\"1.39\" parent=\"/drugs/neomycin-sulfate\">\n<title>Contra-indications</title>\n<body>\r\n<section outputclass=\"contraindications\">\r\n<sectiondiv outputclass=\"additionalContraindications\">\r\n<sectiondiv outputclass=\"cautionsOrContraindicationsWithRoutes\">\r\n<p outputclass=\"title\">When used by ear</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<ph outputclass=\"contraindication\">patent grommet (although may be used by specialists, see <xref format=\"dita\" href=\"#PHP78609\" type=\"bookmark\" namespace=\"/treatment-summaries/ear\">Ear</xref>)</ph>; <ph outputclass=\"contraindication\">perforated tympanic membrane (although may be used by specialists, see <xref format=\"dita\" href=\"#PHP78609\" type=\"bookmark\" namespace=\"/treatment-summaries/ear\">Ear</xref>)</ph>\r\n</p>\n</sectiondiv>\r\n<sectiondiv outputclass=\"cautionsOrContraindicationsWithRoutes\">\r\n<p outputclass=\"title\">With oral use</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<ph outputclass=\"contraindication\">intestinal obstruction</ph> (in adults); <ph outputclass=\"contraindication\">myasthenia gravis (aminoglycosides may impair neuromuscular transmission)</ph>\r\n</p>\n</sectiondiv>\r\n<sectiondiv outputclass=\"cautionsOrContraindicationsWithRoutes\">\r\n<p outputclass=\"title\">With topical use</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<ph outputclass=\"contraindication\">neonates</ph>\r\n</p>\n</sectiondiv>\n</sectiondiv>\n</section>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</body>\n</topic>\n<topic id=\"PHP52753\" outputclass=\"cautions\" rev=\"1.34\" parent=\"/drugs/neomycin-sulfate\">\n<title>Cautions</title>\n<body>\n<section outputclass=\"cautions\">\n<sectiondiv outputclass=\"additionalCautions\">\n<sectiondiv outputclass=\"cautionsOrContraindicationsWithRoutes\">\n<p outputclass=\"title\">When used by ear</p>\n<p>\n<ph outputclass=\"caution\">avoid prolonged use</ph> (in adults)</p>\n</sectiondiv>\n<sectiondiv outputclass=\"cautionsOrContraindicationsWithRoutes\">\n<p outputclass=\"title\">With oral use</p>\n<p>\n<ph outputclass=\"caution\">avoid prolonged use</ph> (in adults)</p>\n</sectiondiv>\n</sectiondiv>\n</section>\n<section outputclass=\"importantAdvice\">\n<title>Cautions, further information</title>\n<sectiondiv>\n<p>Although neomycin is associated with the same cautions as other aminoglycosides it is generally considered too toxic for systemic use. </p>\n</sectiondiv>\n<sectiondiv>\n<p outputclass=\"specificity\">With <ph outputclass=\"route\">topical</ph> use in adults</p>\n<p outputclass=\"title\">Large areas </p>\n<p>If large areas of skin are being treated ototoxicity may be a hazard, particularly in the elderly, and in those with renal impairment.</p>\n</sectiondiv>\n<sectiondiv>\n<p outputclass=\"specificity\">With <ph outputclass=\"route\">topical</ph> use in children</p>\n<p outputclass=\"title\">Large areas</p>\n<p>If large areas of skin are being treated ototoxicity may be a hazard in children, particularly in those with renal impairment.</p>\n</sectiondiv>\n</section>\n</body>\n</topic>\n<topic id=\"PHP52608\" outputclass=\"interactions\" rev=\"1.10\" parent=\"/drugs/neomycin-sulfate\">\n<title>Interactions</title>\n<body>\n<section outputclass=\"general\">\n<sectiondiv>\n<p>Appendix 1 (aminoglycosides).</p>\n</sectiondiv>\n</section>\n</body>\n</topic>\n<topic id=\"PHP52490\" outputclass=\"sideEffects\" rev=\"1.49\" parent=\"/drugs/neomycin-sulfate\">\n<title>Side-effects</title>\n<body>\n<section outputclass=\"specificSideEffects\">\n<sectiondiv outputclass=\"frequencies\">\n<sectiondiv outputclass=\"uncommon\">\n<p outputclass=\"title\">Uncommon</p>\n<sectiondiv outputclass=\"sideEffectsWithRoutes\">\n<p outputclass=\"title\">With oral use</p>\n<p>\n<ph outputclass=\"sideEffect\">rash</ph> (in adults)</p>\n</sectiondiv>\n</sectiondiv>\n<sectiondiv outputclass=\"notKnown\">\n<p outputclass=\"title\">Frequency not known</p>\n<sectiondiv outputclass=\"sideEffectsWithRoutes\">\n<p outputclass=\"title\">When used by ear</p>\n<p>\n<ph outputclass=\"sideEffect\">local sensitivity</ph>\n</p>\n</sectiondiv>\n<sectiondiv outputclass=\"sideEffectsWithRoutes\">\n<p outputclass=\"title\">With oral use</p>\n<p>\n<ph outputclass=\"sideEffect\">impaired intestinal absorption with steatorrhoea and diarrhoea</ph> (in adults); <ph outputclass=\"sideEffect\">increased salivation</ph> (in adults)</p>\n</sectiondiv>\n<sectiondiv outputclass=\"sideEffectsWithRoutes\">\n<p outputclass=\"title\">With topical use</p>\n<p>\n<ph outputclass=\"sideEffect\">sensitisation (cross sensitivity with other aminoglycosides may occur)</ph>\n</p>\n</sectiondiv>\n</sectiondiv>\n</sectiondiv>\n</section>\n<section outputclass=\"sideEffectsAdvice\">\n<title>Side-effects, further information</title>\n<sectiondiv>\n<p>Although neomycin is associated with the same side effects as other aminoglycosides it is generally considered too toxic for systemic use and is poorly absorbed after oral administration.</p>\n</sectiondiv>\n</section>\n</body>\n</topic>\n<topic id=\"PHP52584\" outputclass=\"pregnancy\" parent=\"/drugs/neomycin-sulfate\">\n<title>Pregnancy</title>\n<body>\n<section outputclass=\"generalInformation\">\n<sectiondiv>\n<p outputclass=\"specificity\">With <ph outputclass=\"route\">oral</ph> use</p>\n<p>There is a risk of auditory or vestibular nerve damage in the infant when aminoglycosides are used in the second and third trimesters of pregnancy.</p>\n</sectiondiv>\n</section>\n</body>\n</topic>\n<topic id=\"PHP52637\" outputclass=\"hepaticImpairment\" parent=\"/drugs/neomycin-sulfate\">\n<title>Hepatic impairment</title>\n<body>\n<section outputclass=\"generalInformation\">\n<sectiondiv>\n<p outputclass=\"specificity\">With <ph outputclass=\"route\">oral</ph> use in adults</p>\n<p>Absorbed from gastro-intestinal tract in liver disease&#8212;increased risk of ototoxicity.</p>\n</sectiondiv>\n</section>\n</body>\n</topic>\n<topic id=\"PHP52516\" outputclass=\"renalImpairment\" parent=\"/drugs/neomycin-sulfate\">\n<title>Renal impairment</title>\n<body>\n<section outputclass=\"doseAdjustments\">\n<sectiondiv>\n<p>Adjust dose according to individual patient monitoring.</p>\n</sectiondiv>\n</section>\n<section outputclass=\"generalInformation\">\n<sectiondiv>\n<p>Increased potential for systemic side effects, notably ototoxicity and nephrotoxicity in renal impairment.</p>\n</sectiondiv>\n</section>\n</body>\n</topic>\n<topic id=\"PHP52437\" outputclass=\"monitoringRequirements\" parent=\"/drugs/neomycin-sulfate\">\n<title>Monitoring requirements</title>\n<body>\n<section outputclass=\"monitoringOfPatientParameters\">\n<sectiondiv>\n<p>Renal function should be assessed before starting an aminoglycoside and during treatment.</p>\n<p>Auditory and vestibular function should also be monitored during treatment.</p>\n</sectiondiv>\n</section>\n</body>\n</topic>\n<topic id=\"PHP52425\" outputclass=\"lessSuitableForPrescribing\" rev=\"1.10\" parent=\"/drugs/neomycin-sulfate\">\n<title>Less suitable for prescribing</title>\n<body>\n<section>\n<sectiondiv>\n<p outputclass=\"specificity\">With <ph outputclass=\"route\">topical</ph> use</p>\n<p>Neomycin sulfate cream is less suitable for prescribing.</p>\n</sectiondiv>\n</section>\n</body>\n</topic>\n<topic id=\"PHP3489-medicinalForms\" outputclass=\"medicinalForms\" parent=\"/drugs/neomycin-sulfate\">\n<title>Medicinal forms</title>\n<body>\n<section outputclass=\"licensingVariationStatement\">\n<p>There can be variation in the licensing of different medicines containing the same drug.</p>\n</section>\n<p>Forms available from special-order manufacturers include: oral solution, cream</p>\n</body>\n</topic>\n<parents>\n<xref format=\"dita\" scope=\"local\" type=\"drugs\" href=\"#drugs\" title=\"Drugs\" namespace=\"/drugs\">Drugs</xref>\n</parents>\n<children>\n<xref format=\"dita\" scope=\"local\" type=\"medicinalForm\" href=\"#PHP75751\" title=\"Tablet\" namespace=\"/drugs/neomycin-sulfate/tablet\">Tablet</xref>\n</children>\n<backlinks>\n<xref format=\"dita\" scope=\"local\" type=\"drug\" href=\"#PHP88018\" namespace=\"/drugs/betamethasone-with-neomycin\" title=\"BETAMETHASONE WITH NEOMYCIN\" count=\"1\" rel=\"backlink\">BETAMETHASONE WITH NEOMYCIN</xref>\n<xref format=\"dita\" scope=\"local\" type=\"drug\" href=\"#PHP88046\" namespace=\"/drugs/fluocinolone-acetonide-with-neomycin\" title=\"FLUOCINOLONE ACETONIDE WITH NEOMYCIN\" count=\"1\" rel=\"backlink\">FLUOCINOLONE ACETONIDE WITH NEOMYCIN</xref>\n<xref format=\"dita\" scope=\"local\" type=\"drug\" href=\"#PHP92557\" namespace=\"/drugs/dexamethasone-with-glacial-acetic-acid-and-neomycin-sulfate\" title=\"DEXAMETHASONE WITH GLACIAL ACETIC ACID AND NEOMYCIN SULFATE\" count=\"1\" rel=\"backlink\">DEXAMETHASONE WITH GLACIAL ACETIC ACID AND NEOMYCIN SULFATE</xref>\n<xref format=\"dita\" scope=\"local\" type=\"drug\" href=\"#PHP92560\" namespace=\"/drugs/clobetasol-propionate-with-neomycin-sulfate-and-nystatin\" title=\"CLOBETASOL PROPIONATE WITH NEOMYCIN SULFATE AND NYSTATIN\" count=\"1\" rel=\"backlink\">CLOBETASOL PROPIONATE WITH NEOMYCIN SULFATE AND NYSTATIN</xref>\n<xref format=\"dita\" scope=\"local\" type=\"drug\" href=\"#PHP98628\" namespace=\"/drugs/dexamethasone-with-hypromellose-neomycin-and-polymyxin-b-sulphate\" title=\"DEXAMETHASONE WITH HYPROMELLOSE, NEOMYCIN AND POLYMYXIN B SULPHATE\" count=\"1\" rel=\"backlink\">DEXAMETHASONE WITH HYPROMELLOSE, NEOMYCIN AND POLYMYXIN B SULPHATE</xref>\n<xref format=\"dita\" scope=\"local\" type=\"treatmentSummary\" href=\"#PHP78284\" namespace=\"/treatment-summaries/skin-infections\" title=\"Skin infections\" count=\"1\" rel=\"backlink\">Skin infections</xref>\n<xref format=\"dita\" scope=\"local\" type=\"treatmentSummary\" href=\"#PHP78381\" namespace=\"/treatment-summaries/skin-cleansers-antiseptics-and-desloughing-agents\" title=\"Skin cleansers, antiseptics and desloughing agents\" count=\"1\" rel=\"backlink\">Skin cleansers, antiseptics and desloughing agents</xref>\n<xref format=\"dita\" scope=\"local\" type=\"treatmentSummary\" href=\"#PHP78593\" namespace=\"/treatment-summaries/aminoglycosides\" title=\"Aminoglycosides\" count=\"3\" rel=\"backlink\">Aminoglycosides</xref>\n</backlinks>\n<links>\n<xref format=\"dita\" scope=\"local\" type=\"interaction\" href=\"#bnf_int_133\" namespace=\"/interactions/list-of-drug-interactions/antibacterials/aminoglycosides/neomycin\" title=\"Neomycin\" count=\"1\" rel=\"link\">Neomycin</xref>\n<xref format=\"dita\" scope=\"local\" type=\"treatmentSummary\" href=\"#PHP78609\" namespace=\"/treatment-summaries/ear\" title=\"Ear\" count=\"2\" rel=\"link\">Ear</xref>\n<xref format=\"dita\" scope=\"local\" type=\"#drugs\" href=\"#drugs\" namespace=\"/drugs\" title=\"Drugs\" count=\"1\" rel=\"link\">Drugs</xref>\n<xref format=\"dita\" scope=\"local\" type=\"medicinalForm\" href=\"#PHP75751\" namespace=\"/drugs/neomycin-sulfate/tablet\" title=\"Tablet\" count=\"1\" rel=\"link\">Tablet</xref>\n</links>\n</topic>",
